<title>USA: Harvey Entertainment Co Q1 shr loss.</title>
<headline>Harvey Entertainment Co Q1 shr loss.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>THE HARVEY ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY</p>
<p>			  Consolidated Statements of Operations</p>
<p>					 (Unaudited)</p>
<p>						     Three Months Ended</p>
<p>							   March 31,</p>
<p>							  1997	  1996</p>
<p>Operating Revenues:</p>
<p>   Licensing and Merchandising	  $1,018,000     $825,000</p>
<p>   Filmed Entertainment			763,000    1,434,000</p>
<p> Net operating revenues		    1,781,000    2,259,000</p>
<p> Cost of sales				   632,000	446,000</p>
<p>Selling, general and</p>
<p>   administrative expenses		 1,383,000	714,000</p>
<p>Amortization of film library,</p>
<p>goodwill, trademarks,</p>
<p>  copyrights and other			  88,000	336,000</p>
<p> Depreciation expense			   22,000	 10,000</p>
<p> Total operating expenses		  2,125,000    1,506,000</p>
<p> Other income				     56,000	 72,000</p>
<p>(Loss) income before benefit</p>
<p>  (provision) for income taxes	   (288,000)	825,000</p>
<p> Benefit (provision) for income taxes    105,000    (352,000)</p>
<p> Net (loss) income			   (183,000)	473,000</p>
<p> Net (loss) income per share		  (0.05)	   0.12</p>
<p>Weighted average shares</p>
<p>  outstanding				  3,594,000    3,865,000</p>
<p>We expect our second quarter results will also be impacted by costs associated with building our consumer products and character development infrastructure, the company said.</p>
<p>In the second half of 1997, however, we anticipate improved performance due to the release of our first-ever direct-to-video feature, &quot;Casper, A Spirited Beginning,&quot;  to be distributed by Twentieth Century Fox Home Entertainment, which will position the Company for strong earnings potential.&quot;</p>
</text>
